.TH "HPC\-COMPOSE\-WHEN" "1" "" "hpc\-compose 0.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hpc\-compose\-when \- Submit once cluster conditions are met
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
hpc\-compose when [OPTIONS]
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Prepare and render the compose job now, then monitor Slurm or local wall\-clock conditions in the foreground and submit automatically when every condition is satisfied.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB-f\fR, \fB--file\fR \fIFILE\fR
Compose specification file to read; if omitted, use the active context compose file or fall back to compose.yaml.
.TP
\fB--enroot\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the enroot executable. Default: enroot.
.TP
\fB--apptainer\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the apptainer executable. Default: apptainer.
.TP
\fB--singularity\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the singularity executable. Default: singularity.
.TP
\fB--huggingface\-cli\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the huggingface\-cli used by hf:// stage_in inside the job (default: huggingface\-cli). Default: huggingface\-cli.
.TP
\fB--keep\-failed\-prep\fR
Keep failed preparation state on disk for later inspection.
.TP
\fB--skip\-prepare\fR
Skip image import and prepare reuse checks.
.TP
\fB--force\-rebuild\fR
Refresh imported and prepared artifacts before running.
.TP
\fB--no\-preflight\fR
Skip the preflight phase before running.
.TP
\fB--partition\fR \fIPARTITION\fR
Partition to monitor for \-\-free\-nodes; must match x\-slurm.partition.
.TP
\fB--free\-nodes\fR \fINODES\fR
Submit when the monitored partition has at least this many idle nodes.
.TP
\fB--after\-job\fR \fIJOB_ID\fR
Submit after this Slurm job reaches a terminal state matching \-\-after\-job\-condition.
.TP
\fB--after\-job\-condition\fR \fICONDITION\fR
Dependency condition for \-\-after\-job: afterany, afterok, or afternotok. Default: afterany.
.TP
\fB--between\fR \fIHH:MM\-HH:MM\fR
Submit only inside this local wall\-clock window, e.g. 22:00\-06:00.
.TP
\fB--poll\-interval\fR \fIDURATION\fR
Polling interval for active monitoring; minimum 5s. Default: 60s.
.TP
\fB--timeout\fR \fIDURATION\fR
Give up if conditions are not met within this duration; 0s performs one check.
.TP
\fB--script\-out\fR \fIOUTPUT\fR
Write the rendered launcher script to this path before monitoring.
.TP
\fB--sbatch\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the sbatch executable. Default: sbatch.
.TP
\fB--srun\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the srun executable. Default: srun.
.TP
\fB--sinfo\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the sinfo executable. Default: sinfo.
.TP
\fB--squeue\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the squeue executable. Default: squeue.
.TP
\fB--sacct\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the sacct executable. Default: sacct.
.TP
\fB--allow\-resume\-changes\fR
Allow submission even when resume config drift is detected.
.TP
\fB--detach\fR
Submit and return after tracking metadata is written.
.TP
\fB--watch\-mode\fR \fIMODE\fR
Watch output mode after submission. Default: auto. Possible values: auto, tui, line.
.TP
\fB--hold\-on\-exit\fR \fIWHEN\fR
Keep the watch UI open after terminal states. Default: failure. Possible values: never, failure, always.
.TP
\fB--format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR
Output format for \-\-detach. Possible values: text, json.
.TP
\fB--color\fR \fIWHEN\fR
Controls colored output. Default: auto. Possible values: auto, always, never.
.TP
\fB--quiet\fR
Suppress progress indicators and non\-essential labels.
.TP
\fB--profile\fR \fINAME\fR
Profile name to load from .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB--settings\-file\fR \fIPATH\fR
Explicit settings file path; defaults to upward search for .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Print help (see a summary with '\-h').
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
hpc\-compose when \-f compose.yaml \-\-partition gpu8 \-\-free\-nodes 4
hpc\-compose when \-f compose.yaml \-\-after\-job 12345
hpc\-compose when \-f compose.yaml \-\-between 22:00\-06:00
hpc\-compose when \-\-detach \-\-format json \-f compose.yaml \-\-partition gpu8 \-\-free\-nodes 4
.fi
